gw.api.match

Interface MatchableTreeTraverserConfig


  • public interface MatchableTreeTraverserConfig
    MatchableTreeTraverserConfig Implement this interface to configure which entities and properties are considered Side By Side Data. Provides access to entities that are created, updated or removed as a result of base data copy when accessing Side By Side data. Used by MatchableTreeTraverser

      • shouldCopyBean

        boolean shouldCopyBean(KeyableBean parentBean,
                       KeyableBean targetBean)
        shouldCopyBean Based on the parent bean and target bean, return whether the target bean should be copied. The intent is to provide full access to the parent and child bean in order to allow greater control when determining whether or not to copy a particular bean. NOTE: It is strongly recommended to provide filtering using the other methods in this class as this amount of control also opens the door to creating performance issues during base data copy.
        Parameters:
        parentBean - parent of targetBean
        targetBean - targeted bean
        Returns:
        true if the bean should be copied

      • shouldCopyArrayElement

        boolean shouldCopyArrayElement(KeyableBean targetBean)
        shouldCopyArrayElement Return whether the target bean within an array should be copied. The base implementation returns true if the target bean's type is not configured as side by side It is strongly recommended to provide filtering using the other methods in this class as this amount of control also opens the door to creating performance issues during base data copy.
        Parameters:
        targetBean - targeted bean
        Returns:
        true if the bean should be copied
